<h1 class="ds-page-title">Voice control</h1>
<p class="ds-page-lead">
    Voice control users navigate and interact with interfaces using voice commands.
</p>

<h2>Voice control considerations</h2>
<div class="component-example">
    <div class="component-example-title">Example - Voice-friendly labels</div>
    <button type="button" class="btn btn-primary" id="saveButton">
        Save changes
    </button>
    <button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary" id="cancelButton">
        Cancel
    </button>
</div>

<h2>Guidelines</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Use descriptive, unique labels for all interactive elements</li>
    <li>Avoid generic labels like "Click here" or "Button"</li>
    <li>Ensure buttons and links have clear, action-oriented text</li>
    <li>Provide visible labels that match voice command expectations</li>
    <li>Use consistent naming conventions across the application</li>
    <li>Ensure form inputs have clear, associated labels</li>
    <li>Test with voice control software (Dragon, Voice Control on macOS/iOS)</li>
    <li>Avoid elements that are only identifiable by visual position</li>
</ul>

<h2>Resources</h2>
<ul>
    <li><a href="https://www.w3.org/WAI/WCAG21/Understanding/name-role-value.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">WCAG Name, Role, Value Requirements</a></li>
</ul>
